  <div class="header-question">Privacy Policy</div>
  <p>WCES collects information from applicants, including, but not limited to, names, addresses, email addresses, phone and fax numbers, and information about the educational background and credentials. This information is used in conjunction with the evaluation of an applicant's credentials for purposes of issuing reports. WCES takes an applicant's privacy very seriously, and WCES will take all reasonable steps to protect our applicant's privacy.</p>

  <p>If you communicate with WCES via email or request that WCES communicate with you via email, the contents of your emails to WCES, and WCES's responses, together with your email address, will be retained by WCES.</p>

  <p>Like many websites, WCES also gathers information about how visitors use its website. This information is used only in aggregate and contains no personal identification information. We do not disclose, sell, trade or rent any information obtained in this way to third parties. We may disclose certain aggregate data, such as the number of visitors in a given period or the most frequently accessed pages, to others. In general, you can visit many of our web pages without revealing who you are or any personal information about yourself. WCES may collect information regarding your browser type and IP address when you visit our website.</p>

  <p>However, if you reveal or provide any personal or confidential information, you will no longer be anonymous to WCES. Any confidential or personal information you provide to WCES is treated by applicable laws and according to that stated below.</p>

