  <p>This website contains links to other sites. WCES is not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of such websites. WCES encourages you to review the privacy policies of these websites. Applicants should take such steps as they deem necessary to protect their privacy before linking to these other websites.</p>

  <b class="iH3">Watch out for Phishing</b>
  <p>"Phishing" refers to emails sent to individuals containing authentic-looking messages that instruct them to provide sensitive personal information. Individuals who "bite" are exposed to identity theft. Phishing occurs when an individual receives a deceptively-legitimate looking email from what appears to be a reputable company. The email asks recipients to update their credit card or account information. WCES does not send emails with links to update your information. WCES is not responsible for phishing attempts by identity thieves made which use the WCES name or identification.</p>

  <b class="iH3">Protection of Children's Privacy Online</b>
  <p> WCES's website is not designed to be used by children. WCES does not knowingly collect or use personal information from children under the age of 13 without obtaining verifiable parental consent.</p>

